                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/4773: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-05-11T21:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1927—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 12—1:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>131. Following from Stimson:</p>
                <p>“With Minister Eberhardt, Admiral Latimer and General Feland, have had a second
                    conference today with Moncada and one of his generals <pb facs="0449" n="347"
                        xml:id="pg_347"/> at Tipitapa. I believe we have concluded satisfactorily
                    the final details for the disarmament of the insurgent army which is expected to
                    be completed in two days after which I am invited to meet personally and address
                    it at Las Banderas on Saturday.”<note n="72" xml:id="d328fn72">May 14.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
